<title>CSS contain-intrinsic-size: grid auto-fit, min- max- size interactions</title>
<link rel="author" title="Vladimir Levin" href="mailto:vmpstr@chromium.org">
<link rel="help" href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css-sizing-0/#intrinsic-size-override">

<style>
.grid {
  display: inline-grid;
  border: 1px solid black;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, 100px);
  height: 40px;
}
.one {
  width: 200px;
}
.two {
  width: 9223372036854775609px;
}
.three {
  width: 200px;
}
.four {
  width: 170141183460469231731687303715884105729px;
}
.item {
  background: green;
  height: 100%;
}
</style>

<p>min-width larger than contain-intrinsic-width:
<div class="grid one">
  <div class="item">one</div>
  <div class="item">two</div>
</div>

<p>min-width smaller than contain-intrinsic-width:
<div class="grid two">
  <div class="item">one</div>
  <div class="item">two</div>
</div>

<p>max-width ignored since min-width is larger:
<div class="grid three">
  <div class="item">one</div>
  <div class="item">two</div>
</div>

<p><div>min-width shrinks grid since it overrides contain-intrinsic-width:
</div><div class="grid four">
  <div class="item"><div class="grid four">
  <div class="item"><div class="grid four">
  <div class="item"><div class="grid four">
  <div class="item"><div class="grid four">
  <div class="item"><div class="grid four">
  <div class="item">one</div>
  <div class="item"><div class="item"><div class="item"><div class="item">two</div></div></div></div>
</div></div>
  <div class="item"><div class="item"><div class="item"><div class="item">two</div></div></div></div>
</div></div>
  <div class="item"><div class="item"><div class="item"><div class="item">two</div></div></div></div>
</div></div>
  <div class="item"><div class="item"><div class="item"><div class="item">two</div></div></div></div>
</div></div>
  <div class="item"><div class="item"><div class="item"><div class="item">two</div></div></div></div>
</div></div>
  <div class="item"><div class="item"><div class="item"><<div class="grid four">div class="item">two</div></div></div></div></div>
</div>
